      <hedline>
        <hl1>London Firm Buys Competitive Media</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Taylor Nelson Sofres in London has completed the purchase of Competitive Media Reporting in New York, for $88 million.</p>
        <p>Competitive Media, which tracks advertising expenditure, was sold by VNU, the Dutch publisher that was forced to dispose of the business by the Federal Trade Commission in return for regulatory approval for its acquisition of Nielsen Media Research Inc. in New York.</p>
      </block>
